- \(P(A \text{ or } C) = 1.20 - 0.28 = 0.92\)  
- \(P(\text{neither}) = 0.08\)  
- Total: \(0.92 + 0.08 = 1.00\), which checks out.  

The probability of visiting a physical therapist is 0.68, rounded to two significant figures as per the input values.

