- 17% have an irregular heartbeat (IH).
- Of those with irregular heartbeat, 35% have high blood pressure, so the percentage with both IH and HBP is 35% of 17% = 0.35 × 17 = 5.95%.
- The percentage with normal blood pressure (NBP) is 100% - 16% - 19% = 65%.
- Of those with normal blood pressure, 11% have irregular heartbeat, so the percentage with both IH and NBP is 11% of 65% = 0.11 × 65 = 7.15%.

