Problem: 6.3-5. Let $Y_1 < Y_2 < \cdots < Y_8$ be the order statistics of eight independent observations from a continuous-type distribution with 70 th percentile $\pi_{0.7}=27.3$.
(a) Determine $P\left(Y_7<27.3\right)$.
 The unit of the answer should be  .
Solution: The problem requires finding \(P(Y_7 < 27.3)\) where \(Y_7\) is the seventh order statistic in a sample of eight independent observations from a continuous distribution with the 70th percentile \(\pi_{0.7} = 27.3\).

For a continuous distribution, \(P(Y_7 < 27.3) = P(Y_7 \leq 27.3)\) since the probability of equality is zero. The cumulative distribution function at 27.3 is \(F(27.3) = 0.7\). The event \(Y_7 \leq 27.3\) occurs if at least seven observations are less than or equal to 27.3. The number of observations less than or equal to 27.3 follows a binomial distribution with parameters \(n = 8\) and \(p = 0.7\).

Thus, \(P(Y_7 \leq 27.3) = P(X \geq 7)\) where \(X \sim \text{Binomial}(8, 0.7)\). This is calculated as:
\[
P(X \geq 7) = P(X = 7) + P(X = 8)
\]
\[
P(X = 7) = \binom{8}{7} (0.7)^7 (0.3) = 8 \times (0.7)^7 \times 0.3
\]
\[
P(X = 8) = \binom{8}{8} (0.7)^8 (1) = (0.7)^8
\]

Numerically:
\[
(0.7)^7 = 0.0823543
\]
\[
P(X = 7) = 8 \times 0.0823543 \times 0.3 = 0.19765032
\]
\[
(0.7)^8 = 0.05764801
\]
\[
P(X = 8) = 0.05764801
\]
\[
P(X \geq 7) = 0.19765032 + 0.05764801 = 0.25529833
\]

Rounding to three significant figures, the result is 0.255. The value 27.3 has three significant figures, and the probability 0.7 is exact, so three significant figures are appropriate.

