- \(P(S = 9) = \binom{10}{9} (0.7)^9 (0.3) = 10 \times (0.7)^9 \times 0.3 = 10 \times 0.040353607 \times 0.3 = 0.121060821\)  
- \(P(S > 8) = P(S = 9) + P(S = 10) = 0.121060821 + 0.0282475249 = 0.1493083459\)  
- \(P(S \leq 8) = 1 - 0.1493083459 = 0.8506916541\)  

Since the drugs are identical and independent, \(P(\text{all } S_i \leq 8) = (0.8506916541)^3 \approx 0.6156253804\).  
Thus, \(P(\text{max} > 8) = 1 - 0.6156253804 = 0.3843746196\).

