B & =\{x: x \text { is a } 9,10, \text { or jack and } x \text { is red }\}, \\
C & =\{x: x \text { is a club }\}, \\
D & =\{x: x \text { is a diamond, a heart, or a spade }\} .
\end{aligned}
$$
Find $P(A)$ The unit of the answer should be  .
Solution: The probability of event A, which is drawing a jack, queen, or king, is calculated as follows. There are 12 such face cards in a standard 52-card deck (3 face cards per suit and 4 suits). The probability is the number of favorable outcomes divided by the total number of outcomes, so P(A) = 12 / 52. Simplifying this fraction gives 3/13. Converting 3/13 to a decimal results in approximately 0.230769. Rounded to three decimal places, this is 0.231.

