Solution: The ionization energy of \(\mathrm{H}_2\) is calculated using the dissociation energies and the ionization energy of atomic hydrogen. The relationship is:

\[
\text{IE}_{\mathrm{H}_2} = D_0(\mathrm{H}_2) + \text{IE}_{\mathrm{H}} - D_0(\mathrm{H}_2^{+})
\]

